			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				I'm rather surprised as to how people seem so afraid of these creatures.  After reading the posts, and talking to a few people in the game I decided to join a full group of lvl 16-18 (I was scared at the time) to fight them for silk... We destroyed two red con spiders, then the group broke apart.  After words it was just me (a lvl 16 Necro) and a lvl 16 (not sure the class, but can hide and cast a fear like spell).. We fought and easily killed two red  conned spiders.  All we had to do was dot, and then fear.. Easy picking.  After we split up,  I then fought a yellow con spider and killed it using the same tactic just stated.<BR>
<BR>
I then soloed a yellow con one, and killed that rather easily as well.  I then fought a red one, and was killed by it (my fears where resisted, and  I had a blue pet - does considerably less damage). However, I got it down to less then 1/4 health, if my last fear wasn't resisted I would have beaten.<BR>
<BR>
The spider does hit hard but as long as it is feared, and you have a pet/tank it is a rather easy opponent. <BR>
<BR>
Its poison is rather weak, despite what people have posted, and if you can can get someone to cast endure poison on you, it won't even take hold.
				</font>
			</td>

